      level: 3,
      title: 'Hormonal Contraception Mechanisms',
      content: `Understanding how hormonal contraception works helps women choose the most appropriate method for their needs.

**Mechanisms of Action:**

**Primary Mechanisms:**
1. Inhibit ovulation (primary for combined methods)
2. Thicken cervical mucus (progestin-only)
3. Thin endometrium (makes implantation less likely)
4. Slow tubal motility (affects egg/sperm transport)

**Combined Hormonal Contraceptives (CHC):**

**Estrogen Component (Ethinyl estradiol):**
| Suppresses FSH and LH
| Prevents follicular development
| Inhibits ovulation
| Stabilizes endometrium
| Controls cycle (withdrawal bleeds)

**Progestin Component:**
| Thickens cervical mucus
| Slows tubal motility
| Makes endometrium less receptive
| Backup ovulation suppression

**Progestin-Only Methods:**

**Progestin-Only Pill (POP):**
| Thickens cervical mucus (primary)
| Inhibits ovulation in 40-50% of cycles
| Slows tubal motility
| Must be taken at the same time daily
| No estrogen-related risks

**Levonorgestrel IUD:**
| Thickens cervical mucus
| Slows sperm motility
| Suppresses ovulation in some cycles
| Thins endometrium
| Local effect on uterus

**Etonogestrel Implant:**
| Thickens cervical mucus
| Inhibits ovulation (most cycles)
| Slows tubal motility
| Continuous progestin effect

**Medroxyprogesterone Acetate Injection:**
| Suppresses ovulation
| Thickens cervical mucus
| Thins endometrium
| Persistent effect

**Contraindications to Estrogen-Containing Methods:**

**Absolute Contraindications (WHO Category 4):**
| History of thromboembolism or current thrombosis
| History of stroke or ischemic heart disease
| Migraine with aura
| Breast cancer (current)
| Pregnancy
| Age >35 with smoking
| Prolonged immobility
| Uncontrolled hypertension
| Diabetes with complications

**Relative Contraindications (WHO Category 3/4):**
| Migraine without aura (category 3)
| Well-controlled hypertension (category 3)
| Obesity (BMI ≥30) (category 3)
| Breastfeeding >6 weeks postpartum (category 3)

**Benefits Beyond Contraception:**

**Combined Hormonal Contraceptives:**
| Regular, predictable cycles
| Reduce menstrual bleeding
| Improve dysmenorrhea
| Improve acne
| Reduce ovarian and endometrial cancer risk
| Improve PMS symptoms
| Reduce endometriosis pain

**Levonorgestrel IUD:**
| Lighter periods (or none)
| Reduce dysmenorrhea
| Reduce endometriosis pain
| Treat heavy menstrual bleeding
| Reduce endometrial hyperplasia risk

**Side Effects:**

**Common (usually resolve):**
| Breakthrough bleeding
| Breast tenderness
| Nausea (especially with CHC)
| Headache
| Mood changes

**Serious (rare):**
| Blood clots (estrogen-containing)
| Stroke (estrogen-containing)
| Heart attack (estrogen-containing)
| Liver problems
| High blood pressure
| Breast cancer (small increased risk)
