**Postpartum Contraception:**

**Breastfeeding Women:**

**Safe Options:**
| Progestin-only pill
| Levonorgestrel IUD (can be placed immediately postpartum)
| Etonogestrel implant
| DMPA injection
| Copper IUD (can be placed immediately postpartum)
| Condoms

**Not Recommended Until 6 Weeks Postpartum:**
| Combined hormonal contraceptives
| Because estrogen can affect milk supply

**Non-Breastfeeding Women:**
| All methods safe immediately postpartum
| IUDs can be placed immediately postpartum
| Higher expulsion rates if placed immediately

**Adolescents:**
| LARC methods first-line:
  - High efficacy
  - Long-acting
  - No user action required
  - Reversible
| Confidentiality essential
| STI screening important
| Condoms recommended along with LARC for STI protection

**Perimenopause (Ages 40-50+):**
| Fertility declines but still present until menopause
| Contraception needed for 1 year after last period
| LARC excellent option
| Progestin-only pills
| Low-dose CHC if no contraindications
| Copper IUD (non-hormonal option)

**Medical Conditions:**

**Diabetes:**
| LARC methods safe
| Progestin-only methods safe
| CHC can be used if no vascular complications
| Monitor blood pressure and lipids

**Obesity (BMI ≥30):**
| LARC methods safest and most effective
| Progestin-only pill safe (but higher failure rate)
| CHC possible but higher thrombosis risk
| DMPA associated with weight gain

**Depression:**
| Hormonal methods not contraindicated
| Monitor mood changes
| Some antidepressants interact with CHCs

**Epilepsy:**
| Many anti-epileptics induce liver enzymes
| Enzyme-inducing AEDs reduce CHC effectiveness
| Higher dose CHC needed with enzyme inducers
| LARC not affected by drug interactions
| Progestin-only methods also affected

**Rheumatologic Diseases:**
| SLE with positive antiphospholipid antibodies: avoid estrogen
| RA, SLE without APL: CHC may be used
| LARC safe and effective
| Progestin-only safe

**Contraception After Abortion:**

**Immediate Post-Abortion IUD Placement:**
| Safe for both surgical and medical abortion
| Highly effective
| Reduces repeat abortion risk
| Expulsion rate slightly higher but still low

**Immediate Start:**
| Any method can be started immediately
| Quick start protocols for CHC
| No need to wait for next period

