| Emergency contraception as backup
| Shared decision-making
| Respect patient preferences
| Full information on risks and benefits

**Myths and Facts:**

| Myth | Fact |
|------|------|
| Birth control causes infertility | False - fertility returns quickly after stopping |
| Birth control causes weight gain | Minimal effect; DMPA may cause weight gain |
| You need a "break" from the pill | Not necessary for most modern pills |
| Birth control causes abortion | False - prevents ovulation and fertilization |
| Withdrawal is effective | Only 78% effective with typical use |
| You can't get pregnant while breastfeeding | False; ovulation can return before first period
